<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/815498-is-the-book-hard-to-comprehend-and-uses">Is the book hard to comprehend and uses tough langauge?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_815498'><a id="like_count_community_question_815498" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/815498?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">5 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F46114.The_Waves">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/815498-is-the-book-hard-to-comprehend-and-uses">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/815498-is-the-book-hard-to-comprehend-and-uses">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/69215317-mariana-luna"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1500190949i/69215317._UX100_CR0,12,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/69215317-mariana-luna">Mariana Luna</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s not hard to read if you like detailed descriptions of places and feelings/thoughts; or if you enjoy introspection, since you will be inside chara<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's not hard to read if you like detailed descriptions of places and feelings/thoughts; or if you enjoy introspection, since you will be inside characters' heads (there's no dialogue). It is confusing at the beginning, but once you pass the first pages, it starts to make sense. It doesn't use tough language either. Maybe a couple of words you might look in the dictionary.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

